cessing for a single connection using an `Async` handler.\nThe library-level entry point for running a server is `Server.serve`.\nThis function can be used with a `TCP.Socket` or any other type that implements\n`Transport` to build custom server loops.\n\n# Example\n\n```lean\n-- Create a TCP socket server instance\nlet server ← Socket.Server.mk\nserver.bind addr\nserver.listen backlog\n\n-- Enter an infinite loop to handle incoming client connections\nwhile true do\n  let client ← server.accept\n  background (serveConnection client handler config)\n```\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Server/Connection.html#Std.Http.Server.serveConnection","kind":"def","line":533,"name":"Std.Http.Server.serveConnection","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Std/Http/Server/Connection.lean#L533-L558"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Connection.html#Std.Http.Server.Connection.extensions\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Connection</span>.<span class=\"name\">extensions</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Connection.html#Std.Http.Server.Connection\">Connection</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Std/Http/Data/Extensions.html#Std.Http.Extensions\">Extensions</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Extensions to attach to each request (e.g., remote address).\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Server/Connection.html#Std.Http.Server.Connection.extensions","kind":"def","line":64